title: Five dead, 25 injured in factory fire on Egypt's north coast
text:
A fire at a clothes factory on Monday night in Egypt's Mediterranean governorate of Alexandria took the lives of five workers and left 25 others injured, Al-Ahram Arabic news website reported.
The factory is located in Borg El-Arab, west of the city of Alexandria.
Head of the Alexandria emergency medical department Ibrahim Al-Rouby told Al-Ahram that all the injured have been taken to Amereya Hospital.
Al-Rouby added that 22 of the injured would be discharged soon, while the three others require further treatment.
In a similar incident, a fire in the commercial hub of Haret El-Yahud (Jewish Alley) injured four people late September.
